<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Hwang_Jung-min" title="Hwang Jung-min">Hwang Jung-min</a> as Lee Kang-ok<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
<dl><dd>A bandmaster at a hotel in <a href="/wiki/Names_of_Seoul#Gyeongseong" title="Names of Seoul">Gyeongseong</a>, who chooses to take his only daughter to Japan in order to keep her safe. But they get sent to the Hashima labor camp instead, and there he'll do anything that's asked of him, as long as he can protect his daughter.</dd></dl>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/So_Ji-sub" title="So Ji-sub">So Ji-sub</a> as Choi Chil-sung<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
<dl><dd>The best street fighter in Gyeongseong, a coarse man who constantly stirs up troubles in the labor camp. Under his harsh and rough exterior, he has a good heart.</dd></dl>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Song_Joong-ki" title="Song Joong-ki">Song Joong-ki</a> as Park Moo-young<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
<dl><dd>A member of the <a href="/wiki/Korean_independence_movement" title="Korean independence movement">Korean independence movement</a> who infiltrates the island in order to rescue a fellow independence fighter being held captive there.</dd></dl>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Lee_Jung-hyun" title="Lee Jung-hyun">Lee Jung-hyun</a> as Oh Mal-nyeon</li></ul>
<dl><dd>A <a href="/wiki/Comfort_women" title="Comfort women">comfort woman</a> who gets moved to Hashima after going through endless troubles under the Japanese colonization, but never loosens her strong grip on hope.</dd></dl>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Supporting">Supporting</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Battleship_Island&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Supporting">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Kim_Su-an" title="Kim Su-an">Kim Su-an</a> as Lee So-hee</li></ul>
<dl><dd>Lee Kang-ok's daughter. She was being captured by the Japanese general because of her talents in singing and dancing.</dd></dl>
